# Doing Something

## When to use

State the trigger conditions plainly. Example: "When the user asks to ___,
mentions ___, or provides a file matching ___."

## Steps

1. First step.
2. Second step.
3. Third step.

For deeper material, link supporting files from this SKILL.md — keep
references one level deep (do not chain `a.md → b.md → c.md`). Reference
docs live in `references/`; link every one you ship (an unlinked file is
never loaded — Check 20):

- See [reference.md](references/reference.md) for the full criteria table.
- See [examples.md](references/examples.md) for input/output pairs.

## Output

Describe the expected output shape. If a strict template is required, show it
verbatim. If the format can flex, say so and provide a sensible default.

## Examples

Concrete input → output pairs help much more than abstract descriptions.

## Sidecar files

Layout: governance sidecars (`tests.md`, `test-prompts.md`,
`PROMOTION-CHECKLIST.md`, `goal.md`) sit beside this `SKILL.md`; reference docs
go in `references/`; executable scripts go in `scripts/`. Don't leave reference
docs or scripts loose at the skill root (Checks 18/19).

- `tests.md` — REQUIRED. at least 3 verification scenarios (golden / edge / error; add more as you verify them)
  with a `Last verified:` date. The harness FAILs without this file outside
  `staging/`. See `tests.md.template` in the skeleton.
- `test-prompts.md` — only if you plan to autoresearch-improve this skill.
  Positive + negative trigger fixtures used by `improving-skills`.
- `references/reference.md` — optional. Keep only if the detail would push the
  body toward the ~500-line budget or is needed on demand, not every run. Else
  inline it. Keep each reference file ≤200 lines (Check 16); give any over
  100 lines a `## Contents` table of contents (Check 17).
- `references/examples.md` — optional. Keep only if input/output pairs show what
  prose can't. If the steps are self-evident, skip it.
- `scripts/` — optional. Utility scripts the skill executes (not loaded).
- `PROMOTION-CHECKLIST.md` — the promotion record. Fill it in before copying
  the skill to `.claude/skills/`. See `PROMOTION-CHECKLIST.md.template`.

When in doubt, strip — an unused sidecar is just maintenance surface. Link any
reference you ship from this SKILL.md, one level deep (no chains); an unlinked
file is an orphan Claude never loads (Check 20).

